<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Rideable Beasts Released!!!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Jon">Jon</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:29 p.m. 10/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Rideable Beasts Released!!!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Howdy folks! It's me again, your favourite weirdo, Jon!!! But today i wont be talking about Mr Cow... Today i will be talking about the new selection of rideable beasts and creatured that verant will be releasing next week!!

<BR>They have tried to keep is 'hush-hush' but the word has just gotten out that there are currently several rideable beasts being released sometime next week.... The list is as follows...
<BR>:Horse
<BR>:Elephant (includes wooly mammoth)
<BR>:Brown bear
<BR>:Lion
<BR>:Giant Snake
<BR>:Forager (a new creature,apparently quite large, two-legged, reptilian, and runs faster than a horse)
<P>rumours have it that there are also some others though information is not sufficient. Verant has tried to keep this on a secret, but now it's out i suggest you start saving up for a rideable partner. Of course it is said that some creatures are restricted to certain races and classes.
<BR>(ie the wooly mammoth is entirely restricted to barbarian shaman's)and riding will be a new skill. The skill level determines how fast you can ride and still attack, and not fall off, and whether you can land a large fall without sustaining damage, etc, etc....
<BR>More updates to come!
<BR>Love you all lots
<BR>-Jon
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
